content: May 2 (Reuters) - Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskiy told the Washington Post in an interview published on Tuesday that he had not had any conversations with the White House about a leak of secret U.S. documents that grabbed attention around the world last month.

"I did not receive information from the White House or the Pentagon beforehand," Zelenskiy was quoted as saying."It is unprofitable for us." he added. "It is not beneficial to the reputation of the White House, and I believe it is not beneficial to the reputation of the United States." (Reporting by Costas Pitas in Los Angeles Editing by Chris Reese)
